solutions.content:
I was more familiar with Comparator Classes / Functors and completely clueless about `auto []()`
So here's one without Lambda functions.

**Explaination:**
It is not sufficient to pick out the class with the least pass ratio, add a brilliant kid (extraStudent), and recalculate the average. Although that might seem the best way to solve this "greedily", there may be another class which would have a greater increase/spike in the pass ratio when adding a brilliant kid (this depends on the size of the class). 

I define `spike` as the difference between the current Pass Ratio and the expected increase of the pass ratio in the event an `extraStudent` is added.

So all you have to do is to add a brilliant kid to the class which would have the greatest spike in the pass ratio by "sorting" the Max heap of `studentClasses` with respect to the spike/impact. The class with the highest spike is the one we'd want to greedily add a student to.

```
// Trust me this isn't Java Lol
class studentClass {
public:
    int total,passed; // total strength of the class and number of students that passed
    double passRatio; 
	double expectedIncreaseInPassRatio; // incase an extraStudent / brilliant kid is added
    studentClass(int passed, int total)
    {
        this->passed = passed;
        this->total = total;
        passRatio = (double)passed/total;
        expectedIncreaseInPassRatio = (double)(passed+1)/(total+1); // If an extra studen were to be added
    }
};

// The following class helps the priorty queue in prioritizing its elements
class PassRatioComparator {
public:
	// This as good as passing a comparator into a built in sorting function
    bool operator()(studentClass a, studentClass b) // Overloading the fucntion `()` operator. This is called a Fucntion Object or a Functor.
    {
        double spikeA = a.expectedIncreaseInPassRatio -  a.passRatio;
        double spikeB = b.expectedIncreaseInPassRatio -  b.passRatio;
        return spikeA < spikeB; 
		// ^^ This makes sure that the class with Highest spike is infront of the Priority queue
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    double maxAverageRatio(vector<vector<int>>& classes, int extraStudents) {
        priority_queue<studentClass, vector<studentClass>, PassRatioComparator> maxHeap;
        // ^^ Standard way of declaring a max heap with a comparator class 

        for(auto c: classes)
        {
            studentClass x(c[0],c[1]); 
            maxHeap.push(x);
        }

        while(extraStudents--)
        {
            studentClass x = maxHeap.top(); 
			// ^^ This class has the highest spike/impact on adding an extra student
            maxHeap.pop();
            studentClass y(x.passed+1,x.total+1); 
			// ^^ So create a new class with one extra student. 

			// Now y has a better pass ratio such that:
			// y.passRatio == x.expectedIncreaseInPassRatio

            maxHeap.push(y);
        }

        int n = maxHeap.size();
        double sum=0;
        while(maxHeap.size()>0)
        {
            sum+=maxHeap.top().passRatio;
            maxHeap.pop();
        }
        return sum/n;
    }
};
```
