The goal is that for every student, we want to place him or her in the class that will have the maximal impact on the overall average. To do that, we simply just compare all the difference in ratios if we were to place one student in each class for the incoming student.
```
class Solution:
    def maxAverageRatio(self, c: List[List[int]], e: int) -> float:
        pq = []
        for p, t in c:
            heappush(pq, (-((p + 1) / (t + 1) - (p / t)), p, t))
        while e:
            r, p, t = heappop(pq)
            p += 1
            t += 1
            heappush(pq, (-((p + 1) / (t + 1) - (p / t)), p, t))
            e -= 1
        res = 0
        while pq:
            r, p, t = heappop(pq)
            res += p / t
        return res / len(c)
```

