**Method 2: Greedy Algorithm**
Starting from index `k`, find the max scores of good subarray of size `1, 2, 3, ..., nums.length`, respectively; return the maximum out of them.
```java
    public int maximumScore(int[] nums, int k) {
        int score = nums[k], min = nums[k], lo = k, hi = k, n = nums.length;
        while (lo > 0 || hi < n - 1) {
            if ((lo > 0 ? nums[lo - 1] : 0) < (hi < n - 1 ? nums[hi + 1] : 0)) {
                ++hi;
            }else {
                --lo;
            }
            min = Math.min(min, Math.min(nums[lo], nums[hi]));
            score = Math.max(score, (hi - lo + 1) * min);
        }
        return score;
    }
```
