Same as largest histogram problem, for every range we are checking in largest histrogram we just check if that range contains kth element or not and upadte the result.
The only diff btw the two codes is in this problem we are checking if k lies int the subarray range before updating the result
```
class Solution {
    public int maximumScore(int[] hist, int k) {
        Stack<Integer> st=new Stack<>();
        int res=0;
        for(int i=0;i<hist.length;i++){
            if(st.isEmpty()||hist[i]>=hist[st.peek()])
                st.push(i);
            else{
                int q=st.pop();
                int l=st.isEmpty()?0:st.peek()+1,r=i-1;  
                //current subarray range : [l,r]
				//this if condition is only modification done to largest histogram problem
                if(l<=k&&k<=r)
                    res=Math.max(res,hist[q]*(st.isEmpty()?i:i-1-st.peek()));
                i--;
            }
        }
        while(!st.isEmpty()) {
            int ind=st.pop();
            int l=st.isEmpty()?0:st.peek()+1,r=hist.length-1;
            if(l<=k&&k<=r)
                res=Math.max(res,hist[ind]*(st.isEmpty()?hist.length:hist.length-1-st.peek()));
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

