The idea is to keep track of min element for any subarray from i to j. For that we need to fill an array with minimum element.
First start form index k-1th and go till 0th index and fill minimum element so far in array - 
```
nums = [1,4,3,7,4,5], k = 3
       ^
arr =  [1,3,3,7,-,-]
```
Do the same for (k+1)th index to last index - 
```
nums = [1,4,3,7,4,5], k = 3
       ^
arr =  [1,3,3,7,4,4]
```
Now - 
1. Set left pointer at 0th index and right at last index
2. Calculate result
3. Stop left or right pointer when it reaches at kth index, and move another pointer anyway
4. Move index which has lower min value as we need to maximize the min value to get maximum score.
5. Repeat form 2

```
left = 0, right = 5
[1,3,3,7,4,4]  => result = 6
 ^         ^
[1,3,3,7,4,4] => result = 15
   ^       ^
[1,3,3,7,4,4] => result = 12
     ^     ^
[1,3,3,7,4,4] => result = 12
       ^   ^
[1,3,3,7,4,4] => result = 8
       ^ ^
```
Code:
