solutions.content:
The big idea is we start from the kth index and slide left and right to each end.
To determine which side to slide to, we pick the side with the bigger value as it will always result in a larger result.
Finally, we need to maintain the minimum value of the current array by comparing the latest included value with the known minimum value.

Below is the code:
```
var maximumScore = function(nums, k) {
    const n = nums.length
    let max = nums[k], min = nums[k], i = k, j = k
    while (i >= 0 && j < n) {
        max = Math.max(min * (j - i + 1), max)
        min = (j === n - 1 || nums[i - 1] > nums[j + 1]) ? Math.min(nums[--i], min) : Math.min(nums[++j], min)
    }
    return max
};
```

