solutions.content:
# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We want to maximise our score.So,the first thought should be how to eliminate min values and how to find minimum value in some range.here,some intution of segment tree comes to find min value in some range.
Let's get back to appraoch.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
First put the l and r pointer at the ends of array.Now,lets take some example  arr=[1,4,5,4,1,8,4],and suppose k=2, here initially the minimum value of the range is 1,but to increase our score we will eliminate 1 from both side.Removing only one 1 will not be benficial so remove all values equal to minimum of that range.For this we have to find the last occurence of min value before k and first occurence of minimum value after k,so that after every iteration we can update our l=last occur+1 and r=first occur -1,here you have to take care that the range always lies around k,not outside k.For storing the indexes,first i used vector<vector<int>> but it gave tle so use map<vector<int>> instead.And for taking care of minimum value in range,i used segment tree. And use binary search to find tha first and last occur of any element by bs on vector<int> store in map intially.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
Here,buildTree function takes O(nlogn) time complexity,answerQuery function takes logn time for each query.Find first and last occur of any element will take logn time.So,overall time complexity is O(nlogn)
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
 O(4*N + N +n)~O(N),here N is 100001.
# Code
```
const int N = 100001;
class Solution {

int arr[N], st[4 * N];
#define pb push_back

    void buildTree(int si, int ss, int se) {
        if (ss == se) {
            st[si] = arr[ss]; return;
        }
        int mid = (ss + se) / 2;
        buildTree(2 * si, ss, mid);
        buildTree((2 * si) + 1, mid + 1, se);
        st[si] = min(st[2 * si] , st[(2 * si) + 1]);
    }

    int answerQuery(int si, int ss, int se, int qs, int qe) {

        if (qs > se || qe < ss) return INT_MAX;

        if (qs <= ss && qe >= se) {
            return st[si];
        }
        int mid = (ss + se) / 2;
        int l = answerQuery(2 * si, ss, mid, qs, qe);
        int r = answerQuery((2 * si) + 1, mid + 1, se, qs, qe);

        return min(l, r);
    }
public:
    int maximumScore(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<int> v(n + 1);
        map<int, vector<int>> indexs;

        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            int x = nums[i - 1];
            arr[i] = x;
            v[i] = x;
            indexs[x].pb(i);
        }
        // int k;cin>>k;
        k++;
        buildTree(1, 1, n);
        int maxi = 0, l = 1, r = n;

        auto pred = [&](int mid, vector<int>&dummy) {
            return (dummy[mid] <= k);
        };
        //int op = 100;
        while (true) {
            //cout << l << " " << r << endl;
            if (l > k || r < k) break;
            int mini = answerQuery(1, 1, n, l, r), len = r - l + 1;
            maxi = max(maxi, mini * len);
            if (r == l) break;
            int remove = mini;
            vector<int> dummy = indexs[remove];

            int left = -1, right = dummy.size();
            while (right - left > 1) {
                int mid = (left + right + 1) / 2;
                (pred(mid, dummy)) ? (left = mid) : (right = mid);
            }
            int smaller;
            if (left == -1) { 
                smaller = l;
            } else {     
                smaller = dummy[left] + 1;
            }
            int larger;
            if (right == dummy.size()) {
                larger = r;
            } else {
                larger = dummy[right] - 1;
            }
            // deb(smaller);deb(larger);
            l = max(smaller, l), r = min(larger, r);
        }
        return maxi;
    }
};
```

