solutions.content:
The algorithm is quite similar to [84. Largest Rectangle in Histogram](https://leetcode.com/problems/largest-rectangle-in-histogram/), we find the next smaller element to the right and to the left of the current element. and for each element we find the best value of the score satisfying `i <= k <= j`.

Below is the Java Code for the above approach.

```java
class Solution {
    public int maximumScore(int[] nums, int k) {
        Stack<Integer> st = new Stack<>();
        int n = nums.length;
        int left[] = new int[n];
        int right[] = new int[n];
        Arrays.fill(right, n);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            while(!st.isEmpty() && nums[st.peek()] > nums[i]) {
                int temp = st.pop();
                right[temp] = i;
            }
            st.push(i);
        }

        st.empty();
        Arrays.fill(left, -1);
        for(int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            while(!st.isEmpty() && nums[st.peek()] > nums[i]) {
                left[st.pop()] = i;
            }
            st.push(i);
        }

        int score = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if(left[i] + 1 <= k && right[i] - 1 >= k) {
                score = Math.max(score, (right[i] - left[i] - 1) * nums[i]);
            }
        }
        return score;
    }
}
```

