# Approach
Two Pointer:
Loop invariant: we choose a min number each time and expand as much as possible on both side considering it as min elmenet for the formula. Aftere we have computed ans with this, we elect new min, which will be the max of the number at 2 ends.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int maximumScore(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size(), i = k, j = k , min_ind = k, ans = nums[k];
        while(i>=0 || j < n){
            // traverse left.
            while(i>=0 && nums[i]>=nums[min_ind]){
                i--;
            }

            // traverse right.
            while(j<n && nums[j]>=nums[min_ind]){
                j++;
            }

            // update ans with max len and this min_ind.
            ans = max(ans, nums[min_ind]*(j-i-1));

            //choose min_ind again. ### NOTE: we should only choose the index which has greater value then other, that way we will not miss this element as min element for ans. Other wise we will ignore this case.
            if(i>=0 && j<n){
                if(nums[i]>nums[j])
                    min_ind = i;
                else
                    min_ind = j;
            } 
            else if(i>=0){
                min_ind = i;
            } else {
                min_ind = j;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

