# Approach
Check input string and mark all found digits in vector. Walk vector backwards and return second digit if present.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1) - uses vector of fixed size 10 to store seen digits.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int secondHighest(string s) {
        vector<bool> d(10, false);
        for (char c: s) {
            if (c >= '0' && c <= '9') {
                d[c - '0'] = true;
            }
        }

        bool fistDigitFound = false;
        for (int i = 9;i >= 0;i --) {
            if (d[i] && !fistDigitFound) {
                fistDigitFound = true;
            } else if (d[i] && fistDigitFound) {
                return i;
            }
        }
        return -1;        
    }
};
```

